This is a tutorial of how to use *args and **kwargs For defining the default value of arguments that is not assigned in key words when calling the function:
def func(**keywargs): if &#39;my_word&#39; not in keywargs: word = &#39;default_msg&#39; print(word) else: word = keywargs[&#39;my_word&#39;] print(word) call this by:
func() func(my_word=&#39;love&#39;) you&rsquo;ll get:
default_msg love read more about *args and **kwargs in python: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-args-and-kwargs-in-python-3
